t we don't need to invoke anything afterward since the constructor would already be in action.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class structure and ServiceLoader**\\n\\nI'm considering whether it's okay to have an additional package-private class called `GeneratorTestServiceProvider` in the same file, even though it's not a test class. It might actually be fine. I need to ensure the ServiceLoader provider configuration is correct, including the file for the class name. Maybe creating a custom interface at the top-level could work better. Also, it's crucial that the service type class is visible to both parent and child loaders to avoid issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering ServiceLoader configuration**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether the service type can be any class or interface, and it seems the provider must have a public no-argument constructor. The service configuration resource is named \\\"META-INF/services/java.lang.Runnable,\\\" and it might instantiate successfully. However, I wonder if the global resource could be included in native and ServiceLoader metadata, especially in native-image tests. For arbitrary service providers in a test app, a resource configuration might be necessary, and it could depend on whether the service provider feature is registered.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ejZtbnZex7LbkfLE6K1iW0GO|fc_0c6f8872be074a0a0169ef7950dca08193b74024ec34de7313", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"initialize-at-run-time|buildArgs.add\\('--initialize-at-run-time\" tests/src metadata -S | head -100", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1178, "output": 3563, "cacheRead": 58368, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63109, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777301786512, "responseId": "resp_0c6f8872be074a0a0169ef791b4734819380a3df0bcb5e81a0"}